<item>
            <title>[LU-6199] ldiskfs kernel warnings at ldiskfs_flush_unwritten_io+0x74</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6199</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;new warnings occasionally seen in ldiskfs due to checking code new in upstream ext4 code for el6.6.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;stack traces look like ldiskfs_truncate() ..... -&amp;gt; ldiskfs_flush_unwritten_io()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lustre calls some ext4/ldiskfs entry points without locking i_mutex.  It must do so in order to avoid deadlocks.  This triggers a WARN_ON_ONCE() check that is in el6.6 and newer kernels.  ldiskfs patch series for future kernels took care of this, but the patch series for el6.6 did not.  Need to add a patch to remove the check for ldiskfs on el6.6&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>el6.6 kernels&lt;br/&gt;
</environment>
